context: The FBI is headquartered at the <a0_0>J. Edgar Hoover Building in <b5_0>Washington, D.C.<b5_0/>,<a0_0/> with <b6_0>56<b6_0/> field offices in major cities across the United States. The FBI also maintains over 400 resident agencies across the United States, as well as over <b7_0>50<b7_0/> legal attachés at United States embassies and consulates. Many specialized FBI functions are located at facilities in <a1_0>Quantico, Virginia<a1_0/>, as well as a "data campus" in <a2_0>Clarksburg, West Virginia<a2_0/>, where <a4_0><b8_0>96 million<b8_0/><a4_0/> sets of fingerprints "from across the United States are stored, along with others collected by American authorities from prisoners in Saudi Arabia and Yemen, Iraq and Afghanistan." The FBI is in process of moving its Records Management Division, which processes Freedom of Information Act (<a3_0>FOIA<a3_0/>) requests, to <b9_0>Winchester, Virginia<b9_0/>.
